1
00:00:22,983 --> 00:00:27,279
[breathes deeply, sighing]

2
00:00:29,573 --> 00:00:32,784
- Hi! Hi, cutie.
- Hey. Mom's home!

3
00:00:32,784 --> 00:00:34,703
- [Sylvia] I missed you.
- Hi, Mom.

4
00:00:34,703 --> 00:00:36,621
- How was it?
- Yeah, good.

5
00:00:36,621 --> 00:00:39,165
Amazing. And it only took you
two days to get the hang of it.

6
00:00:39,165 --> 00:00:40,250
Oh.

7
00:00:41,251 --> 00:00:44,254
- So, um, about that...
- Yeah.

8
00:00:44,254 --> 00:00:45,797
Mommy, I have a surprise for you.

9
00:00:45,797 --> 00:00:47,090
- [Simon] Sit down.
- [exclaims]

10
00:00:47,090 --> 00:00:49,593
- Yeah, you gotta see it.
- Okay. [chuckles]

11
00:00:49,593 --> 00:00:54,222
We had to make a slideshow at school
about our hero, and I chose you.

12
00:00:55,181 --> 00:00:56,057
Aw.

13
00:00:56,057 --> 00:00:57,976
["Who Let the Dogs Out" playing]

14
00:00:57,976 --> 00:01:00,020
[Sylvia gasps] Oh.

15
00:01:00,937 --> 00:01:03,773
[Sylvia, Charlie chuckling]

16
00:01:05,775 --> 00:01:07,944
[chuckles]

17
00:01:07,944 --> 00:01:10,780
Wow. Oh. [chuckles]

18
00:01:13,825 --> 00:01:16,286
- Oh. Oh, Mommy loves it.
- It's so good. Thank you, sweetie.

19
00:01:16,286 --> 00:01:19,873
Yeah. It's beautiful.
[sniffles] It's really sweet, honey.

20
00:01:19,873 --> 00:01:22,167
Hey, so tell us, how was day two?

21
00:01:23,418 --> 00:01:28,757
Um, it was... it was good.
It was just the same. Yeah.

22
00:01:28,757 --> 00:01:29,674
- Aw.
- Oh.

23
00:01:33,845 --> 00:01:35,847
["Let the River Run" playing]

24
00:01:46,566 --> 00:01:48,568
[alarm beeping]

25
00:01:48,568 --> 00:01:50,570
[breathes deeply]

26
00:01:50,570 --> 00:01:52,656
[beeping stops]

27
00:01:55,033 --> 00:01:57,786
You can't go wrong, baby.
You look good in all of it.

28
00:02:45,584 --> 00:02:47,586
["Let the River Run" continues on radio]

29
00:02:59,973 --> 00:03:01,182
[song stops]

30
00:03:07,230 --> 00:03:08,690
- Hey.
- [Sylvia] Hey.

31
00:03:08,690 --> 00:03:10,108
[Will] What are you doing here?

32
00:03:11,860 --> 00:03:13,987
- I got fired.
- You did?

33
00:03:13,987 --> 00:03:15,071
Painting.

34
00:03:15,071 --> 00:03:17,741
Oh, my God. They fired you for that?

35
00:03:17,741 --> 00:03:20,201
- Did that just happen right now?
- Yesterday.

36
00:03:20,201 --> 00:03:23,121
Yesterday?
Then why are you dressed like this?

37
00:03:25,165 --> 00:03:26,374
You haven't told Charlie yet.

38
00:03:26,374 --> 00:03:28,877
- You're pretending to have a job still.
- Yeah.

39
00:03:28,877 --> 00:03:31,922
- Why are you doing that?
- I don't know. [stammering]

40
00:03:31,922 --> 00:03:36,259
I just am so embarrassed,
and he got me the job.

41
00:03:36,259 --> 00:03:38,803
- Yeah.
- And he's so perfect. And he's fulfilled.

42
00:03:38,803 --> 00:03:40,972
And I'm just... I-I suck.

43
00:03:40,972 --> 00:03:44,809
You don't suck. No, come on.
That could have happened to anybody?

44
00:03:45,393 --> 00:03:48,980
It happened. And you know what?
[stammers] Who cares?

45
00:03:48,980 --> 00:03:52,275
He will... He'll forgive you.
He'll think it's funny, I bet.

46
00:03:52,275 --> 00:03:53,985
- Yeah.
- Those types of things,

47
00:03:53,985 --> 00:03:56,029
that's why he fell in love with you
in the first place.

48
00:03:56,029 --> 00:03:57,822
- That spark. It's cute.
- Yeah. Yes.

49
00:03:57,822 --> 00:04:00,116
- I think it's funny. He'll laugh about it.
- Yeah. Right?

50
00:04:00,116 --> 00:04:02,160
I think he'll be proud of you.
He'll totally understand.

51
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:03,703
- Yeah.
- He'll be cool with it.

52
00:04:03,703 --> 00:04:05,330
- You're right, he'll be fine. I'll just...
- Yes.

53
00:04:05,330 --> 00:04:07,207
- I'll just go to his work today...
- Yeah.

54
00:04:07,207 --> 00:04:09,542
...and I'll tell him.
And it's important to tell him in person.

55
00:04:09,542 --> 00:04:11,169
Go right now and tell him in person.

56
00:04:11,169 --> 00:04:12,254
- Right? I'll just... Yeah.
- Great.

57
00:04:12,254 --> 00:04:14,631
Well, when he gets home from work tonight.
In person.

58
00:04:14,631 --> 00:04:17,216
- I'll tell him.
- Okay. Tell him tonight. Just tell him.

59
00:04:17,216 --> 00:04:18,300
- Yeah.
- Want some coffee?

60
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:21,054
Yeah... Actually, Will,
he made me a coffee, um, to go.

61
00:04:21,054 --> 00:04:22,138
- Oh, great.
- Yeah.

62
00:04:27,811 --> 00:04:30,105
- You didn't tell him!
- It wasn't an easy night.

63
00:04:30,105 --> 00:04:33,024
The kids were crazy and it was hectic.

64
00:04:33,024 --> 00:04:35,360
So, you were right. I'm not worried.

65
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:37,195
Charlie's so great. It'll be okay.

66
00:04:37,195 --> 00:04:40,865
You have to tell him.
Please. It's getting weird.

67
00:04:40,865 --> 00:04:42,450
It's not getting weird.

68
00:04:42,450 --> 00:04:44,828
It's quite weird,
and I feel like I'm enabling you.

69
00:04:44,828 --> 00:04:45,996
You have to tell him.

70
00:04:45,996 --> 00:04:49,624
You are not allowed in this bar anymore
unless you bring me a note from Charlie

71
00:04:49,624 --> 00:04:52,085
that says he knows you've been fired,
and he knows you're here.

72
00:04:52,085 --> 00:04:53,962
A signed note?

73
00:04:54,629 --> 00:04:56,590
[stammers] Is this <i>The Handmaid's Tale</i>?

74
00:04:56,590 --> 00:05:00,385
A-Am I a-adhering
to your patriarchal dictatorship?

75
00:05:00,385 --> 00:05:02,429
Do you want to know when I'm menstruating?

76
00:05:02,429 --> 00:05:03,972
Just tell him.

77
00:05:06,224 --> 00:05:07,225
Fine.

78
00:05:08,518 --> 00:05:10,353
[Will] No. Come on.
You gotta be kidding me.

79
00:05:10,353 --> 00:05:14,065
Oh, what is this? You got a fucking note?
You got a note from Charlie?

80
00:05:14,065 --> 00:05:16,276
"Will, I'm good with Sylvia hanging
at the bar.

81
00:05:16,276 --> 00:05:21,197
Let's go to another ball game, bro.
Yours, Charlie. PS, go, Dodgers."

82
00:05:21,197 --> 00:05:22,324
Dodgers spelled wrong.

83
00:05:22,324 --> 00:05:24,034
A man did not write this.

84
00:05:24,618 --> 00:05:26,453
Just tell him! Tell him!

85
00:05:26,453 --> 00:05:28,079
- Tell him!
- Fine, I'll tell him!

86
00:05:29,497 --> 00:05:31,708
Just wanna finish my coffee first.

87
00:05:31,708 --> 00:05:33,460
"From the desk of Charles Greeves."

88
00:05:34,085 --> 00:05:35,462
Nice touch.

89
00:05:48,308 --> 00:05:49,392
I have to tell you something,

90
00:05:49,392 --> 00:05:52,153
and I don't know how to say it,
so I'm just going to come out with it.

91
00:05:53,563 --> 00:05:56,691
- I got fired. [sighs]
- Wha... Wh-What happened?

92
00:05:56,691 --> 00:05:58,151
I got, um... uh...

93
00:05:59,277 --> 00:06:01,863
It's, uh, s-such a stupid story.

94
00:06:01,863 --> 00:06:03,114
So, I was just so tired

95
00:06:03,114 --> 00:06:06,034
from all of the work...
so much more than I remembered...

96
00:06:06,034 --> 00:06:09,746
and, um, I, uh, was just really tired.

97
00:06:09,746 --> 00:06:12,415
And I was in the hallway
waiting for the photocopy machine,

98
00:06:12,415 --> 00:06:13,833
and I fell asleep.

99
00:06:13,833 --> 00:06:17,963
And then I fell through a painting
and my elbow went through the canvas,

100
00:06:17,963 --> 00:06:22,175
and it's this, like, really... [sighs]
...expensive painting of Kirk Friedkin.

101
00:06:23,510 --> 00:06:26,638
- Wait, what?
- I know, and I was embarrassed about it.

102
00:06:26,638 --> 00:06:29,432
And I... I know I've been so lost
these last few months,

103
00:06:29,432 --> 00:06:32,519
and all you've tried to do is get me
on a path of being productive,

104
00:06:32,519 --> 00:06:34,646
and I... You know, look at me. [chuckles]

105
00:06:34,646 --> 00:06:37,148
- I'm such a failure.
- No, no, no.

106
00:06:37,148 --> 00:06:39,234
- You are not a failure.
- [whimpers]

107
00:06:39,234 --> 00:06:42,445
- I mean, you fell through a painting?
- [sighs]

108
00:06:42,445 --> 00:06:45,240
Yeah. I'm so stupid.
Thank you for understanding, baby.

109
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:48,994
Yeah. Yeah, I think... I think...
I think I understand.

110
00:06:48,994 --> 00:06:50,078
Yeah.

111
00:06:50,662 --> 00:06:53,206
Look, I mean, you're...
you've been out of the game for a while.

112
00:06:53,206 --> 00:06:55,709
- And there's a reason that, you know...
- Yes.

113
00:06:55,709 --> 00:06:58,044
...only twentysomethings can handle
that kind of a workload.

114
00:06:58,044 --> 00:07:01,548
And I got u-unfairly attacked
by a painting.

115
00:07:02,257 --> 00:07:06,386
Yeah. I mean, Kirk Friedkin, obviously,
he has nothing against you personally,

116
00:07:06,386 --> 00:07:09,222
but, you know,
he has got a business to run.

117
00:07:09,222 --> 00:07:11,308
And it's an unfortunate set
of circumstances

118
00:07:11,308 --> 00:07:13,059
that triangulated around you.

119
00:07:13,059 --> 00:07:16,354
[groans]
You know what? It is a tricky situation.

120
00:07:17,188 --> 00:07:20,650
I can see both sides of it. [sighs]

121
00:07:20,650 --> 00:07:23,612
And then he says to me,
"I can really see both sides, babe."

122
00:07:23,612 --> 00:07:27,699
And I'm, like, all I need to hear is,
"Fuck that job. Fuck Kirk Friedkin."

123
00:07:27,699 --> 00:07:31,828
But instead, I get this whole,
like, undecided voter analysis.

124
00:07:31,828 --> 00:07:33,663
But weren't you the one
that destroyed the painting?

125
00:07:33,663 --> 00:07:38,293
Yes, I understand what I did was wrong,
and I deserve to be fired.

126
00:07:38,293 --> 00:07:41,171
But sometimes I just want Charlie
to take my side, you know?

127
00:07:41,171 --> 00:07:43,048
And not see all sides in an argument.

128
00:07:43,048 --> 00:07:45,342
But it is kind of his job
to see all sides.

129
00:07:45,342 --> 00:07:46,968
- Oh, my God.
- So I get where he's coming from.

130
00:07:46,968 --> 00:07:50,430
Do I have to have another conversation
today where I talk shit about you?

131
00:07:50,430 --> 00:07:53,016
Oh, my God. Andy is so annoying.

132
00:07:53,016 --> 00:07:54,935
- He, like, won't stop texting me.
- [scoffs] Oh.

133
00:07:54,935 --> 00:07:57,604
- Just out of nowhere for no reason.
- [clicks tongue] Really?

134
00:07:57,604 --> 00:08:00,941
He's like, "Babe, you're so beautiful.
Baby, I miss you so much."

135
00:08:00,941 --> 00:08:02,275
- Aw.
- It's, like... [scoffs]

136
00:08:02,275 --> 00:08:04,277
- Just so annoying, right?
- Yeah.

137
00:08:04,277 --> 00:08:07,072
You know what Charlie just texted me?
"Need mayo."

138
00:08:07,072 --> 00:08:09,658
Need mayo? Who n... You don't need mayo.

139
00:08:09,658 --> 00:08:11,618
- Anyway, back to my boyfriend.
- You know? [groans]

140
00:08:11,618 --> 00:08:15,705
He is very sweet,
because out of the blue, last night,

141
00:08:15,705 --> 00:08:18,416
he invited me to San Diego
on a business trip.

142
00:08:18,416 --> 00:08:20,418
- It's so cute he wants me to be there.
- Oh.

143
00:08:20,418 --> 00:08:22,254
Oh, wait. Is that for the bar?

144
00:08:22,254 --> 00:08:25,966
Yeah. It's, like, a...
We're meeting some CEO, Johnny Vroom.

145
00:08:25,966 --> 00:08:27,050
What?

146
00:08:27,551 --> 00:08:29,511
- [sighs] Yeah.
- You get to meet Johnny Rev?

147
00:08:30,095 --> 00:08:32,013
- Yeah, that's him.
- Oh.

148
00:08:32,013 --> 00:08:34,558
Why didn't Will invite me?
I love Johnny Rev.

149
00:08:34,558 --> 00:08:35,933
I don't think he's going.

150
00:08:35,933 --> 00:08:37,561
- Oh.
- I don't know. I have to go buy an outfit.

151
00:08:37,561 --> 00:08:39,604
- Okay. All right.
- Okay, bye.

152
00:08:39,604 --> 00:08:41,523
- Johnny Rev.
- [Katie] Bye.

153
00:08:41,523 --> 00:08:43,441
That's bullshit.

154
00:08:45,110 --> 00:08:46,361
[line ringing]

155
00:08:46,361 --> 00:08:48,530
- [Will] <i>Yo!</i>
- Hey.

156
00:08:48,530 --> 00:08:51,408
Hey, how come Katie gets
to meet Johnny Rev and I don't?

157
00:08:51,408 --> 00:08:52,492
[Sylvia] <i>That's rubbish.</i>

158
00:08:52,492 --> 00:08:54,327
The San Diego thing?
I'm not going on that.

159
00:08:54,911 --> 00:08:56,037
Yeah, we are. Come on.

160
00:08:56,037 --> 00:08:58,373
No, we're not.
I'm not into this corporate shit.

161
00:08:58,373 --> 00:09:00,667
<i>Come on. You're the brewmaster.</i>

162
00:09:00,667 --> 00:09:02,377
<i>You gotta take control of your business.</i>

163
00:09:02,377 --> 00:09:04,838
We'll go down. It'll be fun. Otherwise,
they're gonna take all the credit.

164
00:09:04,838 --> 00:09:07,883
And this is something you've poured
your heart and soul into.

165
00:09:07,883 --> 00:09:09,551
[Will] <i>You just wanna meet Johnny Rev.</i>

166
00:09:09,551 --> 00:09:11,052
Well, so what?

167
00:09:11,052 --> 00:09:14,139
Come on. It'll be fun.
It doesn't mean it's not true.

168
00:09:15,015 --> 00:09:18,768
You know what? You're actually right.
I should go.

169
00:09:18,768 --> 00:09:21,730
And I should prove how indispensable I am
to this team.

170
00:09:21,730 --> 00:09:23,773
And those guys will fucking regret

171
00:09:23,773 --> 00:09:26,318
not cutting me into
this kombucha thing they did.

172
00:09:26,318 --> 00:09:27,652
You're buying the snacks.

173
00:09:28,737 --> 00:09:30,614
Hey, when do you wanna start prepping
that deposition?

174
00:09:30,614 --> 00:09:31,865
Uh, just give me a second.

175
00:09:31,865 --> 00:09:35,619
I need to print out some photos
for Maeve's birthday book.

176
00:09:35,619 --> 00:09:37,579
Using the firm's photo printer?

177
00:09:37,579 --> 00:09:39,164
You know it, dawg.

178
00:09:39,164 --> 00:09:40,248
All right.

179
00:09:41,958 --> 00:09:44,211
Okay, 2020. Check.

180
00:09:46,004 --> 00:09:48,798
2021, check.

181
00:09:49,716 --> 00:09:50,717
[gasps]

182
00:09:53,011 --> 00:09:54,012
What's this?

183
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:58,433
[Will laughing]

184
00:09:58,433 --> 00:09:59,559
When was this?

185
00:10:01,019 --> 00:10:03,063
- [Will laughing]
- [chuckles]

186
00:10:03,063 --> 00:10:05,357
[both laughing]

187
00:10:08,026 --> 00:10:10,070
- [phone beeps]
- [Stewart] <i>Are you finally ready to work?</i>

188
00:10:10,070 --> 00:10:11,404
Can you come to my office?

189
00:10:12,239 --> 00:10:14,115
So, your wife was hanging out
with her boyfriend.

190
00:10:14,115 --> 00:10:15,909
We know this happens. What's the big deal?

191
00:10:15,909 --> 00:10:18,620
It's a very big deal.
It's a monumentally big deal.

192
00:10:18,620 --> 00:10:20,413
Look at the date on the photo.

193
00:10:21,831 --> 00:10:25,126
That's a whole day before she told me
she was fired at Friedkin's firm.

194
00:10:25,126 --> 00:10:26,503
- [sighs]
- Okay.

195
00:10:26,503 --> 00:10:29,923
- So we know she was fired on Tuesday.
- Yes. Tuesday. Late.

196
00:10:29,923 --> 00:10:32,259
- But she waited till Friday to tell me.
- [sighs]

197
00:10:32,259 --> 00:10:35,095
- And here she is on Thursday...
- Yeah.

198
00:10:35,095 --> 00:10:37,305
- ...horsing around with Will.
- [Will laughs]

199
00:10:37,305 --> 00:10:40,267
Meaning she told Will she was fired,
but she hid it from her husband.

200
00:10:40,267 --> 00:10:42,060
What else is she hiding from me?

201
00:10:43,728 --> 00:10:45,647
They're on a trip together right now.

202
00:10:45,647 --> 00:10:47,732
- Where to?
- San Diego.

203
00:10:47,732 --> 00:10:49,985
- What are they doing in San Diego?
- It's a work thing.

204
00:10:49,985 --> 00:10:51,820
- Are you sure?
- I don't know.

205
00:10:51,820 --> 00:10:53,655
I'm calling in the cavalry.

206
00:10:53,655 --> 00:10:55,407
Jackie! Code green.

207
00:10:57,909 --> 00:10:58,910
[sighs]

208
00:10:58,910 --> 00:11:00,161
["Cracker Island" playing]

209
00:11:18,388 --> 00:11:19,222
[Will] Hello.

210
00:11:19,222 --> 00:11:22,350
- [gasps] Sylvia! You made it! [squeals]
- Oh, my God, I'm so excited!

211
00:11:22,350 --> 00:11:23,727
Of course, I wouldn't miss it.

212
00:11:23,727 --> 00:11:25,645
Dude, what the frick
are you doing here, man?

213
00:11:25,645 --> 00:11:28,148
I thought it's important that I be here
for these big decisions.

214
00:11:28,148 --> 00:11:30,483
So that's why you wanna be here.
You wanna fuck this up for us?

215
00:11:30,483 --> 00:11:32,277
No, I don't wanna fuck it up.
I just wanna help.

216
00:11:32,277 --> 00:11:33,403
Honestly, I'm with Reggie.

217
00:11:33,403 --> 00:11:35,447
You too much of a loose cannon.
You be tripping.

218
00:11:35,447 --> 00:11:37,324
Wait, but Sylvia can still come in, right?

219
00:11:37,324 --> 00:11:41,161
I can come in. I... I'm not a loose cannon.
I'm tight. I-I-I'm not a risk.

220
00:11:41,161 --> 00:11:42,621
I don't care what you do, Sylvia.

221
00:11:42,621 --> 00:11:43,830
Okay. Yes. Thank you.

222
00:11:43,830 --> 00:11:45,582
Dude, I'm not letting you in.

223
00:11:45,582 --> 00:11:48,126
- I'm not gonna let you fuck up our big...
- Hey, there.

224
00:11:48,126 --> 00:11:50,003
You must be the gang
from Lucky Penny Brewing.

225
00:11:50,003 --> 00:11:51,254
- We are. Yeah.
- Yes, we are.

226
00:11:51,254 --> 00:11:53,798
Oh, well, welcome to Johnny 66,

227
00:11:53,798 --> 00:11:55,467
where yum happens.

228
00:11:55,467 --> 00:11:57,636
[all] Wow! [laughing]

229
00:11:57,636 --> 00:11:59,888
Thank you. [chuckles]
No one's ever applauded on that.

230
00:11:59,888 --> 00:12:01,431
- Come on in.
- Please don't fuck this up.

231
00:12:01,431 --> 00:12:03,516
I won't. It's where yum happens.

232
00:12:04,851 --> 00:12:06,686
[Reggie] Whoa! Slopp's? I love Slopp's.

233
